Based on the existing model of the ATM switch [10], we present an ATM activation module under continuous IR (Fig. 3
), which includes three components: the ATM dimer, the inactive ATM monomer, and ATM∗. Here, we assume that DSBCs are the main signal transduction from DSBs to the p53-MDM2 feedback loop through ATM activation, and the rate of ATM activation is a function of the amount of DSBCs and the self-feedback of ATM∗. Furthermore, the total concentration of ATM is a constant including the ATM dimer, ATM monomer, and ATM∗
[10].
